Tongue-tie, also known as ankyloglossia, is a condition present at birth where the lingual frenulum, the tissue connecting the tongue to the floor of the mouth, is shorter than normal, limiting the mobility of the tongue. The underlying causes of this condition are not fully understood, but it is believed to be a result of a complex interplay between genetic predisposition and environmental factors.
